<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1756,2036]" box="[151,1108,1756,1781]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1756,1781]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Description.</emphasis>
Female. Forewing length 
<quantity box="[591,659,1757,1780]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
. Head as described above for the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1756,2036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
Thorax: Dorsum with appressed scaling, presumably brown. Ventral side lighter in color. No trace of forewing pattern; traces of two patches of raised scales in identical positions on both forewings: one below the discal cell between the bases of M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[426,434,1879,1893]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">3</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[546,554,1879,1893]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">1</subScript>
, the other inside discal cell at base; some ill-defined intervenular patches of scales at costal level suggest the presence of a developed strigulae system.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1756,2036]" box="[199,1264,1939,1964]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Abdomen: Tergites covered by wings. Sternites with appressed scales concolorous with thorax.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1756,2036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1975,2000]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heikkilä &amp; Brown &amp; Baixeras &amp; Mey &amp; Kozlov" authorityYear="2018" box="[328,608,1975,2000]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Antiquatortia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="histuroides">
<emphasis box="[328,608,1975,2000]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Antiquatortia histuroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poinar &amp; Brown" authorityYear="1993" box="[901,1091,1975,2000]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Polyvena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horatis">
<emphasis box="[901,1091,1975,2000]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Polyvena horatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but is clearly discriminated by the generic-level characters discussed above in the generic diagnosis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="50" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,151,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is a feminine singular adjective based on the genus name 
<taxonomicName authority="Razowski" authorityName="Razowski" authorityYear="1981" box="[1205,1411,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Histura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1205,1291,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Histura</emphasis>
Razowski
</taxonomicName>
, a diverse genus of 
<taxonomicName box="[341,467,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Polyorthini">Polyorthini</taxonomicName>
in Central America, with the suffix “–oides”, meaning “similar to”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
